<CSS_font-faceFont-display>
<summary>
The <strong><c>font-display</c></strong> descriptor for the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face"><c>_font-face</c></see> at-rule determines how a font face is displayed based on whether and when it is downloaded and ready to use.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-family">@font-face/font-family</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-stretch">@font-face/font-stretch</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-style">@font-face/font-style</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-weight">@font-face/font-weight</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-feature-settings">font-feature-settings</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-variation-settings">@font-face/font-variation-settings</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/src">@font-face/src</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/unicode-range">@font-face/unicode-range</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-display"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value><blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><strong>Note:</strong> In Firefox, the preferences <c>gfx.downloadable_fonts.fallback_delay</c><br/>and <c>gfx.downloadable_fonts.fallback_delay_short</c> provide the duration<br/>of the &amp;quot;short&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;extremely small&amp;quot; periods, respectively.</blockquote></value>
</CSS_font-faceFont-display>
